Movie: Gusto Kita with All My Hypothalamus

Review: There's just so many loop holes; and my biggest question is this: How could a festival that happens every 90 years decide to end the lives of 72 year olds just once every 90 years when all its members could turn 72 years old within 90 years?BUT I really like the trippiness and uniqueness of this Aster film. Brings horror in broad daylight and wonderfully brings psychedelic feels in most scenes. Shockfest. Great cinematography!Florence Pugh is just amazing,…

Movie: The Strange Thing About the Johnsons
Review: Classic Ari Aster proving himself to be the thriller genius that he is right now. A gripping family thriller.
Made unimaginably realistic. Fit for the preference of this new generation and at the same time, a tribute to the young at heart who fell in love with the original animated film.
Best film as an excuse for an adult to cry like a baby.
